narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend this class to students who have a strong foundation in Russian. As a student without a great foundation in Russian, I struggled with the fast pace. Otherwise, it was a fun class and I took a lot out of it.

I would definitely recommend this class. Iâd say this was one of my favorite class so far at Yale. My Russian has improved a lot, as was the purpose of the course. All the readings weâve done have been enjoyable and everything assigned is all useful, not busy work. Overall, very positive experience. Highly recommend.

Yes I would definitely recommend it. The course does exactly what it sets out to do: it builds your grammar and vocabulary so that you can write essays; it involves a lot of reading which improves your ability to do just that; it develops your speaking skills, especially emphasizing the difference between formal and informal speech.
